n-like mechanisms or normalization steps even when not explicitly defined. Evaluation shows that AMA outperforms static decomposers in long-term interpretability and generalization, successfully transferring modules between domains (e.g., using a damping module from mechanics to stabilize RL reward shaping). This work bridges symbolic AI, meta-learning, and cognitive abstraction, offering a pathway toward machines that don't just compute but *understand* through accumulated insight.",
